summary: Dedicated and skilled professional with experience as a Cash Administrator and Customer Service Specialist. Known for prioritizing and handling multiple tasks, delivering high-quality results on time, with little supervision. Energetic, organized, and professional, with strong interpersonal and problem-solving abilities.

experience.title: Cash Office Administration
experience.description: Managed cash inventory and office budgeting for supplies; handled telephone, e-mail, fax and front-desk reception in a high-volume environment; developed and implemented effective filing systems to accelerate paperwork; maintained status reports for customer projects; compiled daily budget reports, organizational charts and company data reports using VeriBalance functions; identified customer needs, built trust, and resolved problems to maximize efficiency.

experience.title: Aviation Electrician
experience.description: Performed scheduled and unscheduled maintenance on 10 F/A-18C aircraft electrical systems and related equipment; promoted to Work Center Training Petty Officer (April 2012); maintained training records for over 19 personnel; achieved multiple qualifications and was selected Plane Captain of the Quarter; volunteered for aircraft maintenance; progressed to greater responsibilities; engaged in Ground Support Equipment qualifications in May 2011.

experience.title: Cashier
experience.description: Assessed customer needs and answered questions; cleaned and organized work area; issued receipts; prepared and organized register supplies; unboxed new merchandise; rotated stock; operated cash register proficiently; provided professional and courteous service; worked overtime during busy periods.

experience.title: Delicatessen
experience.description: Greeted customers; delegated tasks to team members to optimize productivity; handled products and equipment per safety and sanitation guidelines; fulfilled special order requests (e.g., dinners and party platters); safely used knives, scales, wrappers, compactors, garbage disposals, pallet jack and hand trucks; organized product cases in the produce warehouse and walk-in cooler; served shoppers promptly and courteously.

experience.title: Customer Service Representative
experience.description: Worked as a team member performing cashier duties, product assistance and cleaning; expressed appreciation and invited customers to return; upsold additional menu items, beverages and desserts to increase restaurant profits; addressed customer needs and effectively resolved food or service issues; recorded customer orders and repeated them back in a clear, understandable manner.

experience.title: Sales Associate
experience.description: Assessed customer needs and responded to questions; cleaned and straightened work area; issued receipts for purchases; organized register supplies; unboxed new merchandise; rotated stock; operated cash register; provided professional and courteous service; worked overtime during busy periods.

experience.title: Sales Associate
experience.description: Greeted customers; delegated tasks to team members to optimize productivity; handled products and equipment in line with safety and sanitation guidelines; fulfilled special order requests; safely used knives, scales, wrappers, compactors, garbage disposals, pallet jack and hand trucks; organized product cases in the produce warehouse and walk-in cooler; served shoppers promptly and courteously.

education.degree: Associate of Applied Science in Paralegal
